Heat your #oven{} to 200C. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a
#garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into 8 wedges. Halve
any larger @broccoli florets{200} so they are all similar sizes. In a #small
bowl{} mix the @hoisin sauce{64%g} with the @soy sauce{25%g} and garlic.

Pop the @British chicken breasts{2} and half the hoisin mixture into a high
sided #roasting tin{} with a drizzle of @oil{}. Mix well to make sure everything
is coated.

> Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Roast for ~{15%minutes} on the middle shelf of your oven.

Meanwhile pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan{} and bring
to the boil. When boiling, add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, stir in the
@Jasmine rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave
to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the
rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Once the chicken has been cooking for ~{10%minutes}, add the broccoli
florets and red onion to the #baking tray{} and mix them into the chicken.
Return to the oven and roast until the broccoli is just tender and slightly
browned on the edges and the chicken is cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a #medium frying pan{} over medium heat. Add the
@sesame seeds{15%g} (no oil) and cook until golden, stirring regularly,
~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the pan and set aside. Pop your pan back on
medium heat and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot add the
@all the greens veg side{200%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{}, then pop a #lid{} (or some #foil{}) on
the pan and leave to steam-fry until the green veg are just tender,
~{6-8%minutes}. Remove to a #plate{} and cover with foil to keep warm. Just
before the chicken is ready, add the remaining sauce mixture to the
#frying pan{} and simmer for ~{1%minute} on medium heat, until thickened
slightly. Add a splash of water to loosen if you like.

> If you've decided to add the green veg side to your meal, once the sesame
> seeds are removed from your pan, pop your pan back on medium heat. Add a
> drizzle of oil and once hot add the all greens veg side to the pan and
> season with salt and pepper. Add a splash of water, then pop a lid (or some
> foil) on the pan and leave to steam-fry until the green veg are just tender,
> 6-8 mins. Remove to a plate and cover with foil to keep warm. Continue with
> the step and recipe as instructed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between #plates{}. Serve with the
chicken, onion and broccoli on top, pouring over any juices from the roasting
tin. Serve the green veg on the side. Reheat the sauce if needed then spoon
over the sauce and scatter over the toasted sesame seeds. Enjoy!